    <section id="id9736876">
      <title>[LO 1.3, 2.1]</title>
      <para id="id8691286">One of the things that change most from day to day is the weather. The weather influences our decisions about where we would like to live, the clothes that we wear and the things that we do. </para>
      <para id="id8801659">We always want to know what the weather will be like. We therefore regularly look at the weather forecasts on television, and listen to it on the radio and read about it in the newspapers. </para>
      <para id="id7546410">Discuss this in your group and suggest some reasons for wanting to know what the weather will be like.</para>
      <para id="id9737577">What is weather actually?</para>
      <list id="id8902723" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Warmth and sunlight travel through the earthâ€™s atmosphere. The rays of the sun affect the air in four different ways: It changes the temperature, the humidity, the air pressure and the wind.</item>
